Keynote Panel Discussion - OPEN TO ALL 
Thursday, February 5, 2015
9:00AM - 10:00AM

Examining the Legal Ethics of the Chevron-Ecuador Pollution and RICO Cases
Join us for this "no holds barred" discussion as our panelists share their views and experiences concerning one of the most high-profile rulings of the United States District Court for the Southern District of New York in 2014. Don't miss this opportunity to hear from key players including:

- Steven Donziger, the lawyer who won a multibillion dollar judgment in Ecuador against Chevron; The twenty-year lawsuit culminated in a ruling by Ecuador's Supreme Court in 2013  ordering Chevron to pay for oil-related environmental damages that impacted the indigenous population. In response, Chevron countersued Mr. Donziger and 47 named plaintiffs in a civil case under the Racketeer Influenced and Corrupt Organizations (RICO) Act.  In a non-jury trial, Judge Kaplan ruled in favor of the oil company, prohibiting Mr. Donziger from collecting his legal fees and the Ecuadorian villagers from enforcing their judgment anywhere in the United States. Mr. Donziger and his attorneys have appealed to the Second Circuit Court of Appeals and separately are helping the villagers pursue collection
 actions against Chevron assets in Canada, Brazil, and Argentina.

- Reed Brodsky, one of the leading trial attorneys representing Chevron at trial against Donziger, the former lead federal prosecutor of Raj Rajaratnam and Rajat Gupta, and now partner in Gibson, Dunn & Crutcher's New York Office

- Journalists Paul M. Barrett, an Assistant Managing Editor and Senior Writer at Bloomberg Business week and the author of Law of the Jungle; and Michael D. Goldhaber, a Senior International Correspondent at The American Lawyer and the author of Crude Awakening: Chevron in Ecuador; who have each covered the case extensively

- Karen Hinton, President of Hinton Communications and an advocate and former spokesperson for the Ecuadorians suing Chevron

The discussion will be facilitated by Patrick Oot, a partner at Shook, Hardy & Bacon and the Chair of the Legaltech Educational Advisory Board.
This is one session that you don't want to miss!

